{"cursor":"6955","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Flocculation', in the field of chemistry, is a process wherein colloids come\nout of suspension in the form of floc or flakes by the addition of a clarifying\nagent. The action differs from precipitation in that, prior to flocculation,\ncolloids are merely suspended in a liquid and not actually dissolved in a\nsolution. In the flocculated system, there is no formation of a cake, since all\nthe flocs are in the suspension.\n","linknr":-1,"url":"flocculation","recorded":1363523444,"links":[],"instances":["geology","chemistry","disambiguation","chemistry","disambiguation","chemistry"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Metallurgy","Chemical processes","Sewerage","Water treatment","Separation processes"],"headings":["Term definition","Applications","Deflocculation","See also","References","({{NoMoreLinks}})","","Further reading"],"image":[],"tags":[["suspension","chemistry"],["precipitation","chemistry"],["coagulation","disambiguation"],["coalescence","chemistry"],["aggregation","disambiguation"],["coagulation","disambiguation"],["deposition","geology"]],"members":["deposition","coalescence","aggregation","precipitation","coagulation","suspension"],"related":["Chemistry","Colloid","Suspension_(chemistry)","Clarifying_agent","Precipitation_(chemistry)","Solution","IUPAC","Particle_aggregation","Coagulation_(disambiguation)","Coalescence_(chemistry)","Colloid_chemistry","Particulate","Settling","Filtration","Emulsion","Civil_engineering","Earth_sciences","Structure","Clay","Slurry","Biology","Curd","Cheese","Rennet","Micelle","Einstein_relation_%28kinetic_theory%29","Gaithersburg,_Maryland","Water_purification","Drinking_water","Sewage_treatment","Viscosity","Dispersant","Anionic","Polymers","Clay","Polyphosphate","Lignosulfonates","Quebracho_tannin","Activated_sludge","Submersible_mixer","Aggregation_(disambiguation)","Algaculture","Clay-water_interaction","Coagulation_(disambiguation)","Drilling_mud","Isoelec